te that I might adjust metadata to focus on field lists instead of all fields, but I need to keep in mind how `getDeclaredFields` works when iterating.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring field retrieval methods**\\\\n\\\\nI need to focus on using `Field.get` for static `VerificationType` fields. I’m wondering if using a fields list with `getDeclaredFields` in native will only return registered fields. It might only return fields related to access, especially if I emphasize static `VerificationType` fields. However, the code also checks `getType` and `getModifiers`, which can affect the population of the constants map. To narrow down metadata, it might be better to list fields explicitly, avoiding the broader scope of all declared fields.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating placeholder situation**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about a generic placeholder that seems to be a test file not properly mapped. It appears the existing placeholder isn't generated for the dynamic report, and only dynamic-access report classes might be generated one-to-one. I’m leaning towards deleting it, but I should verify this. I'm considering using \\\\\\\"git diff --cached,\\\\\\\" but maybe that's not necessary. I think I might just decide to finalize without taking that action.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented coverage for `io.smallrye.classfile.impl.verifier.VerificationType`.\\n\\nChanges:\\n- Added dedicated test file:\\n  - `tests/src/io.smallrye.classfile/jdk-classfile-backport/26/src/test/java/io_smallrye_classfile/jdk_classfile_backport/VerificationTypeTest.java`\\n- The test builds an invalid class via the public `ClassFile` API and verifies it, forcing `VerificationType.toString()` to format the operand stack mismatch:\\n  - Covers `Class#getDeclaredFields()`\\n  - Covers `Field#get(Object)`\\n- Added Native Image reflection metadata for `VerificationType`:\\n  - `metadata/io.smallrye.classfile/j